#. type: Content of: <chapter><title>
#: en/time.xml:7
msgid "Time related functions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: en/time.xml:10
msgid "Setting up business hours, holidays and time zones"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/time.xml:13
msgid ""
"Some functions in OTRS, like escalations and <link linkend=\"unlock-tickets"
"\">automatic unlocking of tickets</link>, depend on a proper configuration "
"of business hours, time zones and holidays.  You can define these via the "
"<link linkend=\"sysconfig\"> SysConfig interface </link> , in <link linkend="
"\"Framework:Core::Time\">Framework &gt; Core::Time</link>.  You can also "
"specify different sets of business hours, holidays and time zones as "
"separate 'Calendars' in <link linkend=\"Framework:Core::Time::"
"Calendar1\">Framework > Core::Time::Calendar1</link>, until <link linkend="
"\"Framework:Core::Time::Calendar9\">Framework > Core::Time::Calendar9</"
"link>.  Calendars can be defined on <link linkend=\"adminarea-queue\">queue</"
"link> or on SLA levels. This means that, for example, you can specify a "
"calendar with 5 x 8 business hours for your 'standard' SLA, but create a "
"separate calendar with 7 x 24 support for your 'gold' SLA; and to have a "
"calendar for your 'Support-USA' queue with a different time window than your "
"'Support-Japan' queue.  OTRS can handle up to 99 different calendars."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/time.xml:36
msgid "Business Hours"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/time.xml:39
msgid ""
"Set up the working hours for your system in SysConfig <link linkend="
"\"Framework:Core::Time:TimeWorkingHours\"> Framework> Core::Time::"
"TimeWorkingHours </link> or for your specific calendar, in the calendar's "
"configuration.  OTRS can handle a granularity of one hour. Checking the "
"marks in the boxes 8, 9, 10 ... 17 corresponds with business hours of 8 AM - "
"6 PM."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/time.xml:48
msgid ""
"Only during the business hours: tickets can escalate, notifications for "
"escalated and pending tickets will be send and tickets will be unlocked."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/time.xml:55
msgid "Fixed date holidays"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/time.xml:58
msgid ""
"Holidays that are on a fixed date every year, such as New Year's Day and "
"Fourth of July, can be specified in <link linkend=\"Framework:Core::Time:"
"TimeVacationDays\"> TimeVacationDays </link> or in the corresponding section "
"for the calendars 1-9."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/time.xml:67
msgid ""
"Tickets will not escalate nor get unlocked on dates defined in "
"TimeVacationDays."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><note><para>
#: en/time.xml:72
msgid ""
"By default, OTRS ships with the <emphasis>German</emphasis> holidays "
"installed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><title>
#: en/time.xml:80
msgid "TimeVacationDaysOneTime"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/time.xml:83
msgid ""
"Holidays that do not have a yearly fixed date, such as Easter, can be "
"specified in <link linkend=\"Framework:Core::Time:TimeVacationDaysOneTime\"> "
"TimeVacationDaysOneTime </link> ."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/time.xml:91
msgid ""
"Tickets will not escalate and will not be unlocked on dates defined in "
"TimeVacationDaysOneTime."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><note><para>
#: en/time.xml:97
msgid ""
"OTRS does not ship with any One-Time holidays pre-installed.  This means "
"that you need to add holidays, such as Eastern or Thanksgiving, to the "
"system when configuring OTRS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: en/time.xml:109
msgid "Automated Unlocking"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/time.xml:112
msgid ""
"Locked tickets can be automatically unlocked by the system. This feature "
"might be useful if, for example, an agent has locked tickets that need to be "
"processed, but he can't work on them for some reason, like being on "
"vacation.  The automated unlock feature unlocks tickets after a given time, "
"to ensure that no locked tickets will be forgotten and other agents can "
"process them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/time.xml:120
msgid ""
"The amount of time before a ticket is unlocked can be specified in the <link "
"linkend=\"adminarea-queue\"> settings </link> for every queue. The module "
"<filename>bin/otrs.UnlockTickets.pl</filename>, which is executed "
"periodically as a cron job, performs the automated unlocking of tickets."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/time.xml:132
msgid ""
"Notifications on unlocked tickets are send out only to those agents that "
"have the queue with the unlocked tickets set in \"My queues\" and that have "
"activated the notification on unlocked tickets in their personal <link "
"linkend=\"user-preferences\"> preferences </link> ."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/time.xml:143
msgid "Tickets will be unlocked if all of the following conditions are met:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/time.xml:149
msgid ""
"There is an <emphasis>unlock timeout</emphasis> defined at the queue the "
"ticket is in."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/time.xml:155
msgid "The ticket is set to <emphasis>locked</emphasis>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/time.xml:160
msgid "The ticket state is <emphasis>open</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/time.xml:166
msgid ""
"The unlock timer will be reset if an agent adds a new external article to "
"the ticket, It can be of any of the following types: <emphasis>email-"
"external</emphasis>, <emphasis>phone</emphasis>, <emphasis>fax</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>sms</emphasis>, or <emphasis>note-external</emphasis>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/time.xml:173
msgid ""
"Also, if the last article in the ticket is created by an agent, and a "
"customer adds another one, either via web or email response, the unlock "
"timer will be reset."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: en/time.xml:178
msgid ""
"The last event that will reset the unlock timer is when the ticket is "
"assigned to another agent."
msgstr ""

