#. type: Content of: <chapter><title>
#: en/acl.xml:4
msgid "Access Control Lists (ACLs)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><para>
#: en/acl.xml:7
msgid ""
"From OTRS 2.0 on, Access Control Lists (ACLs) can be used to control access "
"to tickets, modules, queues, etc. or to influence actions on tickets "
"(closing, moving, etc.)  in certain situations. ACLs can be used "
"supplementary to the existing permission system of <link linkend=\"adminarea-"
"roles\"> roles </link> and <link linkend=\"adminarea-groups\"> groups </"
"link> Using ACLs, rudimental workflows within the system can be mapped, "
"based on ticket attributes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><para>
#: en/acl.xml:27
msgid ""
"So far, ACLs cannot be created using the <link linkend=\"adminarea-sysconfig"
"\" > SysConfig interface </link> but must be directly entered into the "
"<filename>Kernel/Config.pm</filename> file. Find some examples below "
"(Example 18-1, 18-2 and 18-3):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><para><example><title>
#: en/acl.xml:39
msgid ""
"ACL which only allows to move tickets with ticket priority 5 into a queue."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><para><example><programlisting>
#: en/acl.xml:43
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    # ticket acl\n"
"    $Self->{TicketAcl}->{'ACL-Name-2'} = {\n"
"        # match properties\n"
"        Properties => {\n"
"            # current ticket match properties\n"
"            Ticket => {\n"
"                Queue => ['Raw'],\n"
"                Priority => ['5 very high'],\n"
"            }\n"
"        },\n"
"        # return possible options (white list)\n"
"        Possible => {\n"
"            # possible ticket options (white list)\n"
"            Ticket => {\n"
"                Queue => ['Alert'],\n"
"            },\n"
"        },\n"
"    };\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: en/acl.xml:38 en/acl.xml:66 en/acl.xml:113 en/stats.xml:867
#: en/stats.xml:903
msgid "<placeholder type=\"example\" id=\"0\"/>"
msgstr ""

